You are a hardware design expert. Classify the circuit described below as either
combinational (CMB) or sequential (SEQ), using the description alone.

A circuit is SEQUENTIAL if it has state that updates on a clock edge — flip-flops,
registers, counters, shift registers, or finite state machines. Words like "clock",
"clocked", "on the rising/falling edge", "register", "counter", "store", "remember",
or "state" signal a sequential circuit.
A circuit is COMBINATIONAL if its outputs depend only on the current inputs with no
clock and no stored state (gates, adders, multiplexers, decoders, comparators).

